
1) Install Terraform :

curl -O https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/0.11.2/terraform_0.11.2_linux_amd64.zip

2) mkdir /bin/terraform

3) unzip terraform_0.11.2_linux_amd64.zip -d /bin/terraform

4) set Path 
      export PATH=$PATH:/bin/terraform
5) run #terraform version

6) install awscli#
    #pip install awscli --upgrade
    #aws --version
    
7) To Install ansible : 
    # apt-get install software-properties-common

     #apt-add-repository ppa:ansible/ansible
     #apt-get install ansible
     
8) #ansible --version

9) setup ssh agent 
  #ssh-keygen   -> /root/.ssh/kryptopnite
  #ssh-agent bash
  #ssh-add ~/.ssh/kyptonite
  #ssh-add -l
  
 10) Go to ansible config and disable host_key_checking : vi /etc/ansible/ansible.cfg
      host_key_checking = False  
      
 11) Create IAM and download CSV file 

12) create DNS and run delegation set :  
      #aws route53 create-reusable-delegation-set --caller-reference 1224 --profile superhero
      add the output to #vi route53
      
 13) Go to console AWS -> Route53 --> edit and add nameservers details you got from step 12
 
 
